---
description: Internal Flutter brownfield defaults for repositories using the shared mobile overlay
globs: ["**/*.dart", "**/pubspec.yaml", "**/.fvmrc", "android/**", "ios/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Read `docs/ai/20-mobile-backend-fastapi-ai.md` and `docs/ai/30-quality-gates.md`.

If the repository also includes the internal mobile overlay, read:
- `ai_docs/standards/flutter-architecture.md`
- `ai_docs/standards/flutter-code-style.md`
- `ai_docs/standards/flutter-testing.md`
- `ai_docs/standards/flutter-ci-deploy.md`
- `ai_docs/standards/brownfield-mobile-adoption.md`

Defaults:
- prefer the repo's chosen structure mode
- use package imports for local app code
- route app screens through the central router
- keep DI in `GetIt` + `Injectable`
- run build_runner when generated files are required
- keep release and generated-files policy explicit
